    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "Partial lifting of Belarusian restrictions imposed due to the outbreak of foot-and-mouth disease cases in the EU" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# Partial lifting of Belarusian restrictions imposed due to the outbreak of foot-and-mouth disease cases in the EU

Partial lifting of Belarusian restrictions imposed due to the outbreak of foot-and-mouth disease cases in the EU
Announcements
2026-05-22
Change in the scope of Belarusian restrictions for animals susceptible to foot-and-mouth infection.

I would like to inform you that in accordance with the decision published on the official website of the Department of Veterinary and Food Supervision of the Ministry of Agriculture and Food of the Republic of Belarus, the restrictions introduced due to the occurrence of cases of foot-and-mouth disease in the EU territory (Germany, Hungary) have been partially lifted.

In connection with the above, I would like to inform you that
The ban has been lifted
import into the Republic of Belarus
of bovine animals and small ruminants originating in the territories of EU Member States.

On the other hand, the ban
transit through the territory of the Republic of Belarus
of bovine animals and small ruminants originating in the territories of the EU Member States
remains in force
.

At the same time, I would like to remind you that
Belarusian import restrictions introduced due to the occurrence of bluetongue disease in Poland are still in force
concerning, m.in, cattle and small ruminants.
)

