tsd:news_padi_web_lutte_contre_la_grippe_aviaire_un_projet_pilote_au_zoo_de_la_palmyre_en_charente_maritime_1779718267 a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:lutte-contre-la-grippe-aviaire-un-projet-pilote-au-zoo-de-la-palmyre-en-charente-maritime-1779718267" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "02ffd7c23b576f4f1a84d8b0889a19340979d7b08b3facaa61551f3879525302" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "Fight against avian influenza: a pilot project at La Palmyre zoo in Charente-Maritime" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# Fight against avian influenza: a pilot project at La Palmyre zoo in Charente-Maritime

Fight against avian influenza: a pilot project at La Palmyre zoo in Charente-Maritime

"It is a vaccine that is closer to the strains circulating today and that makes it possible to distinguish the antibodies of a vaccinated bird from those of a bird infected wi

h the disease. It's very interesting in terms of the epidemiology and monitoring of avian flu in our colonies, offering the possibility of seeing if a bird has been exposed to the virus within the zoo," says ------------------, one of the three veterinarians at the La Palmyre zoologica

l park.This autumn, professionals vaccinated some 70 birds:  American rheas, Cape penguins and ostriches. "These species were chosen b

cause they posed a problem with the vaccine usually used, which we had to redo every six months," says the veterinarian. La Palmyre Zoo is one of the six French animal parks t

o participate in the vaccination campaign led by the Ceva Wildlife Research Fund (Ceva WRF) and the French Association of Zoological Park Veterinarians. A pilot project that aims to evaluate the protection offered by a new vaccine d

veloped by the pharmaceutical laboratory Ceva, by collecting data on the immune response of the species concerned. Three groups have been targeted in this programme – spheniscidae (penguins), ratites (ostri

hes, emus, etc.) and birds of prey – based in particular on their susceptibility to the disease and their conservation value. 

This article has been truncated. Subscribe to read the full article on our website.

