    ts:sourceContentHash "d36bbc266453fd640cca2721acec3bd2f3d28b4a3644d220284be64523e6d8c4" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "Manoeuvres in Prague: An American with suspected Ebola is in the Czech Republic" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# Manoeuvres in Prague: An American with suspected Ebola is in the Czech Republic

Manoeuvres in Prague: An American with suspected Ebola is in the Czech Republic

An American doctor cared for patients with colleagues in the Congo.

Then he flew to Uganda, where he received news that one of his compatriots had developed symptoms of Ebola.

His illness was later confirmed by an examination in Berlin, where he was transported at the request of the United States.

And because another similarly specialized workplace exists in the Czech Republic, the American side approached the Ministry of Health on Tuesday afternoon to see if our experts would take on an American from Uganda, who has not yet shown any signs of infection.

"I am convinced that we should help our partners and allies," said Health Minister Adam Vojtěch (ANO), who decided to admit the patient.

The U.S. will pay for transportation and hospitalization.

Why Europe?
From European countries, the United States asked for help only the Czech Republic and Germany, which accepted six Americans.

Among them is a man who is demonstrably ill.

The Czechs will take care of one.

"The rapid response was possible thanks to the top medical expertise in the Czech Republic, specialized medical facilities and a long tradition of international cooperation in the field of healthcare, including cooperation with the United States," said U.S. Ambassador to the Czech Republic Nicholas Merrick.

They were not transported to America for simple reasons – distance, the difficulty of evacuation and the need for immediate care.

Exercise of the IRS in Nelahozeves - EBOLA

Exercise of the IRS in Nelahozeves - EBOLA • HZS ČR

For the time being, for observation
The patient will be taken care of by the Bulovka University Hospital.

"We will not carry out any tests or examinations yet.

At the moment when the patient does not have symptoms, no tests will prove whether he is in the incubation period or not," explained the head of the clinic, Hana Roháčová.

Even if they did, they could come out negative, even though he could be infected.

The incubation period is 2 to 21 days.

The immune system goes crazy
Ebola is a disease from the family of haemorrhagic fevers, the virus attacks the immune system, which "goes crazy" and causes a so-called cytokine storm.

It floods the body with cytokine protein and attacks all tissues instead of infected cells.

Organs fail, blood stops clotting, blood vessels break down.

The disease begins as the flu, later comes bleeding from the nose, from the mouth, from the rectum.

"Then there is liver and kidney failure, and then the patient dies.

The mortality rate ranges from 10 to 50 percent," says leading infectologist Associate Professor Pavel Dlouhý, adding that there is no cure for the virus.""" ;
    ts:sourcePublishedDate "2026-05-21"^^xsd:date ;
    ts:sourcePublisher "PADI-web" ;
    ts:sourceRetrievedAt "2026-05-28T19:55:28.972775+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    ts:sourceURL "https://www.ahaonline.cz/clanek/musite-vedet/234237/manevry-v-praze-american-s-podezrenim-na-ebolu-je-v-cesku.html"^^xsd:anyURI .

tsd:news_padi_web_medvet_e_pemv_v5_reforcam_informacao_sobre_medicamentos_veterinarios a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:medvet-e-pemv-v5-reforcam-informacao-sobre-medicamentos-veterinarios" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "4022c4b479b9fb44452f2e5641a4bf1d664ad903cde22890caf40e01b0030bb7" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "MedVet and PEMV v5 strengthen information on veterinary medicines" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# MedVet and PEMV v5 strengthen information on veterinary medicines

MedVet and PEMV v5 strengthen information on veterinary medicines
The DGAV makes available, on the MedVet and PEMV v5 platforms, new information on the marketing status of veterinary medicines with antimicrobials, reinforcing support for clinical decision making and the responsible use of these products.
Read more...

The Directorate-General for Food and Veterinary Medicine (DGAV) has made available, on the MedVet Platform and on the Medical-Veterinary Electronic Prescription Platform (PEMV v5), information on the marketing status of presentations of veterinary medicines containing antimicrobials.

This evolution allows veterinarians and economic operators to access additional relevant data at the time of prescription and dispensation, promoting more informed and sustained decisions.

It is important, however, to underline that this functionality is exclusively informative, not conditioning the possibility of prescribing presentations that are not commercialized, and the legal framework in force remains fully applicable.

The DGAV plans to progressively extend this information to other categories of veterinary medicines, as the data available on the MedVet Platform are consolidated.

MedVet and PEMV thus assert themselves as central instruments in monitoring the use of antimicrobials in animals, actively contributing to their prudent use and to the fight against antimicrobial resistance, within the framework of the "One Health" approach.

The DGAV will continue to ensure the continuous evolution of these platforms, reinforcing the quality of the information available and supporting professionals in the sector.

May 22, 2026""" ;
    ts:sourcePublishedDate "2026-05-22"^^xsd:date ;
    ts:sourcePublisher "PADI-web" ;
    ts:sourceRetrievedAt "2026-05-28T19:54:18.976062+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
