Compensatory measure for the recognition of the qualification of BIOLOGIST obtained abroad – July 2026 session
Compensatory measure for the recognition of the qualification of BIOLOGIST obtained abroad – July 2026 session
SHARE
Share
Release Date
25/05/2026

The compensatory measure (aptitude test) for the recognition of the qualification of BIOLOGIST, obtained abroad, will be held at the Department of Biology and Biotechnology "C. Darwin" Sapienza, via dei Sardi 70 - Rome - Aula Tatò (room code RM024-E01P02L117), Edificio Sede San Lorenzo Dip.

BBCD on:
2 July 2026 at 11.00 a.m.: written test and, afterwards, the oral test will take place for candidates who are eligible for the written tests;
Only those who have already received the managerial decree awarding the compensatory measure with the relative transmission note, to whom, however, no letter of convocation will be sent, will be able to apply to participate in this exam session.

The information necessary to participate in the compensatory measure, the related application form and the procedures for carrying out the tests are contained respectively in the files indicated below.

Information on how to participate in the compensatory measure
Application form
Personal data sheet
(to be sent exclusively to the university)
Methods of carrying out tests BIOLOGISTS
Download the study orientation programs of the various subjects covered by the exams.

Biological analysis (urine, exudates, excrement, blood, serological and immunological)
Genetics
Analysis and control of water intended for human consumption
Evaluation and analysis of environmental parameters (water, soil, air)
Identification of pathogens in humans, animals and plants, foodstuffs, paper, wood and artistic heritage
Identification and Testing of Goods of Biological Origin
Design, construction management and testing of plants in the environmental sector
Classification and biology of animals and plants and assessment of their nutritional and energy needs
Environmental impact assessment with regard to biological aspects
Assessment of man's nutritional and energy needs
