tsd:news_padi_web_polli_vaccini_e_terapie_geniche_lesperto_spiega_come_la_nuova_sperimentazione_potrebbe_passare_dai_nostri_piatti_il_caso_html a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:polli-vaccini-e-terapie-geniche-lesperto-spiega-come-la-nuova-sperimentazione-potrebbe-passare-dai-nostri-piatti-il-caso.html" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "60714903f3ee24c943fceba1ba4fdfff67d2dc245a30617f6c529528e3c8a077" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "Chickens vaccinated with gene technologies: the expert explains how the new experimentation could pass through our dishes with unpredictable effects" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# Chickens vaccinated with gene technologies: the expert explains how the new experimentation could pass through our dishes with unpredictable effects

Chickens vaccinated with gene technologies: the expert explains how the new experimentation could pass through our dishes with unpredictable effects

Leonardo Guerra, molecular biologist, expert in gene therapies, mRNA, EMA authorization processes and vaccines, with several decades of research and development on infectious diseases and collaborations with public bodies behind him: what is happening to chickens?
L.G.:

The Ministry of Health, last February, announced a mandatory vaccination campaign against avian influenza, with Veneto as the leader, on 200 farms in the region.

Farms with less than 250 animals are excluded.

Keep in mind that Veneto is the main producer of derivatives of turkeys, chickens, eggs, etc.

I was curious and looked for information, especially about the technology they wanted to use.

And what did he find?

I did not find a single piece of information in all the newspapers, nor in the interviews given by the experts of the Ministry, by the communicators involved, by the Department of Agriculture of the Veneto Region or by the Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute of Veneto.

What did he do?

I called them asking for information on the technologies used, since the authorities had talked about them a lot.

We were in mid-February and the experimentation would have started on April 1st.

And what did they answer you?
Not to be able to talk about it, until the publication in the Official Gazette of the MinSal device.

Why?
I asked for it too.

We are among technicians: I expected them to tell me if it was a traditional vaccine, an attenuated virus or whatever.

Instead they told me no, that they couldn't tell me until everything was published in the Official Gazette.

How strange.

I would say that this is a strange reaction, given that we are colleagues.

We come from five years in which they made fun of us, denied us information and told us that the anti-Covid vaccine was safe and effective, only to then invoke military secrecy.

So what do I do?

I go on Google and look for those in Europe who have had vaccinations against avian flu.

After a lot of research, I pulled out the cards and discovered that a gene technology had been approved in EMA, with an exceptional and therefore experimental procedure, a vaccination against avian flu.

From what can be seen in the EMA documents, and from the little information available, the procedure did not complete the safety tests, required by the standards of the authorization process.

"Exceptional conditions" means that they are not normal.

A viral vector technology (Trojan horse to ensure transfection in the cell cytoplasm, inside the cells of the host's body in each district and organ), used during Covid with the AstraZeneca vaccine in humans.

At that point what does he do?

I begin to ask for an audience with politicians and technical representatives, but everyone avoids.

So we decide, as a group of people, to send a warning to the Veneto Regional Council and to the leaders of the Region, also informing the Meloni government.

In summary, we say: we believe that it is not appropriate to proceed until you explain to us what is happening.

How is it possible that we have been managing avian flu for a hundred years with safe, effective and economical health measures, which do not involve risks for farms, entrepreneurs (regional refreshments), or humans, and then we decide to carry out an experiment of this magnitude and potential impacts on human health without even telling ourselves what it is?
We eat chickens and their derivatives.

In fact, I simply ask: can you explain to me why you abandon a safe, effective and inexpensive method to start a mass vaccination with 14 million doses to be administered provided for by the first version of the MinSal device, also considering the imposing costs that all this entails?

With experimental gene vaccines there is a biological risk, highlighted in humans, of: encephalopathies, encephalitis, prion diseases, aberrant proteins and amyloids: five categories of particularly serious and disabling diseases, with a very slow and insidious incubation, difficult to diagnose even for an experienced neurologist, but with an inauspicious outcome.

But focusing on prions alone, we have a more than concrete veterinary history there.

And did someone answer you?

The Councillor for Agriculture of the Veneto Region.

He told me that the technicians had assured him that everything was "safe and effective".

But how is such safety possible when there is insufficient data on either safety or efficacy?

And I asked: how do you make an experimental treatment mandatory?

In addition, I found written in the documents that this procedure alleviates the symptoms, but does not stop the spread of the virus.

Yet it was mandatory for all farms with more than 250 heads.

I asked where the meaning was in all this.

Reactions?

Even the councilor replied to me: "You're right, it's true, I was at the""" ;
