    ts:sourceContentHash "987f37eddc226aa0a8c3fe6b834d84005b6d3f8f3077e02b9703382f18ab7c1b" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "China imposes a total ban on poultry imports from Brazil due to bird flu" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# China imposes a total ban on poultry imports from Brazil due to bird flu

China imposes a total ban on poultry imports from Brazil due to bird flu

Read in Russian
China imposes a total ban on poultry imports from Brazil due to bird flu

China has banned the import of all types of poultry products from Brazil.

This happened after an outbreak of bird flu was detected in the exporting country.

China's customs agency has said that direct and indirect imports of all poultry and related products from Brazil are prohibited to prevent the "import" of bird flu.

They also added that all plants and animal waste arriving from Brazil must be disinfected.

According to Bloomberg, a large-scale ban by China, the largest buyer of Brazilian chicken meat, is clouding export prospects from this South American country.

This comes even as the two countries work to strengthen relations amid the ongoing global trade war launched by US President ------------.

Earlier this month, Brazil suspended chicken shipments to China and EU countries for 60 days.

This happened after the first case of highly pathogenic avian influenza was registered on a commercial farm in this South American country.

Bloomberg also noted that the bird flu outbreak led to the suspension of trade worth more than $1 billion.

Brazil, which accounts for about a third of global chicken meat exports, reportedly sent more than 10% of its products to China in 2024, according to the Ministry of Agriculture.

According to Chinese customs, the volume of bilateral trade in 2024 amounted to about $1.5 billion.""" ;
    ts:sourcePublishedDate "2026-05-21"^^xsd:date ;
