tsd:news_padi_web_publicado_o_decreto_lei_n_o_103_2026_relativo_aos_controlos_oficiais a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:publicado-o-decreto-lei-n-o-103-2026-relativo-aos-controlos-oficiais" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "90ae4eafc6ce83320dc17567bb640728e8b3634d7054761fa0dcbf000faff0a0" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "Decree-Law No. 103/2026 on official controls published" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# Decree-Law No. 103/2026 on official controls published

Decree-Law No. 103/2026 on official controls published
Decree-Law No. 103/2026 was published, which ensures the implementation, in the national legal order, of Regulation (EU) 2017/625 on official controls and other official activities carried out to verify compliance with the applicable legislation in the areas of food and feed, animal health and welfare, plant health and plant protection products.

The diploma updates and harmonises the national legal framework applicable to official controls, in line with the legal framework of the European Union, strengthening the articulation between the different competent authorities and clarifying mechanisms for coordination, supervision and execution of official controls.

The Directorate-General for Food and Veterinary Medicine remains the competent authority in the areas covered by the diploma, ensuring the coordination, supervision, audit and control of the national system of official controls, in compliance with the principles of independence, impartiality, technical rigor and protection of public health.

The diploma also provides, under the terms already established by Regulation (EU) 2017/625, the possibility of delegating certain official control tasks or related to other official activities, under strict conditions, always maintaining the responsibility and supervision of the competent authority.

The implementation of any mechanism provided for in the diploma will depend on the conditions, limits and guarantees defined by the competent authority, under the terms of the applicable European and national legal framework.

This new framework contributes to strengthening the coherence, efficiency and robustness of the national system of official controls, promoting high standards of food safety, animal health, animal welfare and plant health, essential for consumer protection and for the enhancement and competitiveness of the Portuguese agri-food sector.

Decree-Law No. 103/2026 can be consulted in the Official Gazette at:
https://diariodarepublica.pt/dr/detalhe/decreto-lei/103-2026-1125313602
May 26, 2026""" ;
    ts:sourcePublishedDate "2026-05-26"^^xsd:date ;
