    ts:sourceURL "https://bauernzeitung.at/artikel/oberosterreich/tierseuchen-kennen-keine-grenzen"^^xsd:anyURI .

tsd:news_padi_web_tinh_phu_tho_moi_gom_dia_phan_hoa_binh_vinh_phuc_cu_du_tru_hon_1_trieu_lieu_vaccine_phong_benh_gia_suc_gia_cam a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:tinh-phu-tho-moi-gom-dia-phan-hoa-binh-vinh-phuc-cu-du-tru-hon-1-trieu-lieu-vaccine-phong-benh-gia-suc-gia-cam" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "cdbe077e4a27f10045762a564eeddbb5866db9524aef35b650c5c797d132d1da",
        "d101ba35166e74e1c987d6766f86e082b6d2e899fa37c53c7040dd0786dfac3c" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "The newly created Phu Tho province (which includes the former provinces of Hoa Binh and Vinh Phuc) has stockpiles of more than 1 million doses of vaccines against livestock and poultry diseases.",
        "The newly formed province of Phu Tho (which includes the former provinces of Hoa Binh and Vinh Phuc) has a stockpile of more than 1 million doses of vaccines against livestock and poultry diseases." ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# The newly created Phu Tho province (which includes the former provinces of Hoa Binh and Vinh Phuc) has stockpiles of more than 1 million doses of vaccines against livestock and poultry diseases.

The newly created Phu Tho province (which includes the former provinces of Hoa Binh and Vinh Phuc) has stockpiles of more than 1 million doses of vaccines against livestock and poultry diseases.

Phu Tho province is stockpiling vaccines and taking proactive measures to prevent disease outbreaks among livestock.

Phu Tho Province currently has a large reserve of animal disease prevention and control, including approximately 60,000 doses of foot-and-mouth disease vaccine, one million doses of avian influenza vaccine, 10,000 doses of lumpy skin vaccine, 50,000 doses of rabies vaccine, and about 15,000 liters of disinfectant.

It is considered a critical resource that allows the local community to proactively respond to outbreaks of large-scale diseases.

The biosafe pig breeding model of -----------------'s family in Phu Tho Province.

Photo:

Hoan Nguyen

According to the Department of Agriculture and Environment of Phu Tho Province, the prevention and control of animal diseases has recently received decisive action from all levels of government and with the assistance of the people.

The Provincial Party Committee and the Provincial People's Committee have issued many directives to deal with dangerous infectious diseases such as rabies, African swine fever, bird flu, and lumpy skin disease of cattle and buffalo.

The specialized agency has also developed outbreak control procedures, allowing the use of disinfectants in high-risk areas, and established inspection teams to monitor disease prevention efforts at the local level.

The Department of Livestock, Veterinary Medicine and Fisheries coordinated with local authorities to help people implement disease prevention measures, closely monitor disease progression, and promptly report any unusual signs.

Regarding rabies, the authorities have focused on solving this problem in areas where positive samples have been detected.

From the province's vaccine reserves, 1600 doses of rabies vaccine were distributed to contain and control the outbreak.

All dogs and cats eligible for vaccination in the affected areas have been vaccinated, allowing for a 100% vaccination rate.

To proactively prevent and control diseases in livestock and poultry, as well as prevent the risk of spreading outbreaks, Phu Tho Province ensures the synchronized implementation of comprehensive sanitation, disinfection and vaccination of its animals.

Photo: Hoan Nguyen

According to experts, mass vaccination helps increase herd immunity in livestock and reduces the risk of transmission of rabies to humans, an infectious disease with almost absolute mortality if it develops.

Meanwhile, as far as African swine fever is concerned, outbreaks have been detected and eliminated in the early stages.

The Department of Agriculture and Environment of Phu Tho Province provided 600 liters of disinfectant to the settlements free of charge for disinfecting and treating livestock and barn premises.

Currently, the situation with the disease is largely under control.

Strengthen measures to combat diseases of livestock, poultry and aquatic animals in Phu Tho.

Along with animal husbandry, the local agricultural sector is also strengthening disease surveillance in aquaculture.

According to the plan, environmental monitoring and disease surveillance measures are organized three times a year in concentrated aquaculture areas to quickly detect potential disease outbreaks.

However, the authorities believe that the risk of an outbreak remains high due to unpredictable weather conditions, a large number of livestock and the indifference of part of the population to disease prevention.

In view of this situation, local authorities are advised to intensify efforts to promote biosecurity in livestock and encourage people to proactively vaccinate their animals regularly.

Livestock farmers in Phu Tho Province receive continuous technical training to be able to respond proactively to disease outbreaks in a timely manner.

Photo: Hoan Nguyen Livestock breeders are also advised to supplement the diet of their animals and aquatic species with vitamins and minerals to strengthen their immunity during prolonged hot weather and transitional seasons, when diseases are more likely to break out.

---------------, Deputy Director of the Department of Agriculture and Environment of Phu Tho Province, noted that vaccination, disinfection and rapid response to infectious disease outbreaks continue to be identified as key tasks to minimize damage to the livestock industry.

According to Mr. Lin, localities need to resolutely introduce the declaration and issuance of identification numbers for livestock farms in accordance with the Livestock Law, creating the basis for digital transformation in agriculture and providing support to people in the event of disease outbreaks.

At the same time, the agricultural sector encourages the application of science and technology and the effective management of the aquaculture environment to develop livestock production in a safe and sustainable direction.

According to -----------, Deputy Director of the Department of""",
        """# The newly formed province of Phu Tho (which includes the former provinces of Hoa Binh and Vinh Phuc) has a stockpile of more than 1 million doses of vaccines against livestock and poultry diseases.

The newly formed province of Phu Tho (which includes the former provinces of Hoa Binh and Vinh Phuc) has a stockpile of more than 1 million doses of vaccines against livestock and poultry diseases.

Phu Tho province is stockpiling vaccines and taking preventive measures to prevent outbreaks of disease among livestock.

Phu Tho Province currently has a large stockpile of animal disease prevention and control products, including approximately 60,000 doses of FMD vaccine, one million doses of avian influenza vaccine, 10,000 doses of nodular skin disease vaccine, 50,000 doses of rabies vaccine and about 15,000 litres of disinfectant.

This is considered a critical resource for local authorities to respond quickly to large-scale disease outbreaks.

A model of biosafe pig breeding by ----------------'s family in Phu Tho province.

Photo: Hoan Nguyen.

According to the Department of Agriculture and Environment of Phu Tho Province, animal disease prevention and control have recently been resolutely developed at all levels of government and with the support of the population.

The Provincial Party Committee and the Provincial People's Committee have issued many directives to combat dangerous infectious diseases such as rabies, African swine fever, avian influenza, and nodular skin disease in cattle and buffalo.

The specialized agency has also developed procedures for responding to disease outbreaks, allowing the use of disinfectants in high-risk areas, and has established inspection teams to monitor disease prevention efforts at the local level.

The Department of Livestock, Veterinary Medicine and Fisheries coordinated with local authorities to assist the population in implementing disease prevention measures, closely monitor the development of the disease and immediately report any unusual signs.

As for rabies, the authorities have focused on controlling the problem in areas where positive test results have been found.

1600 doses of rabies vaccine have been distributed from the province's reserves to contain and control the outbreak.

All dogs and cats to be vaccinated in the affected areas have been vaccinated, resulting in 100% vaccination coverage.

To proactively prevent and control diseases in livestock and poultry, and to prevent the risk of large-scale outbreaks, Phu Tho Province ensures the coordinated implementation of comprehensive animal sanitation, disinfection and vaccination measures.

Photo: Hoan Nguyen

According to experts, mass vaccination helps to increase herd immunity in livestock and reduces the risk of rabies transmission to humans, an infectious disease with almost absolute mortality if it develops.

Meanwhile, with regard to African swine fever, outbreaks have been detected and contained at an early stage.

The Futo Provincial Department of Agriculture and Environment provided 600 litres of disinfectant free of charge to local authorities to disinfect and treat livestock and livestock facilities.

Currently, the situation with the disease is mostly under control.

Strengthen disease control measures for farm, poultry and aquatic animals in Phu Tho Province.

Along with animal husbandry, the local agricultural sector is also stepping up disease monitoring in aquaculture.

According to the plan, environmental monitoring and epidemiological surveillance activities are organized three times a year in areas with a high concentration of aquaculture to quickly identify potential outbreaks of diseases.

However, authorities believe that the risk of an outbreak remains high due to unpredictable weather conditions, large livestock populations and the carelessness of part of the population regarding disease prevention.

In light of this situation, local authorities are urged to step up efforts to ensure biosecurity in livestock production and encourage regular vaccination of animals.

Livestock farmers in Phu Tho Province receive continuous technical training to enable them to respond early and quickly to disease outbreaks when they occur.

Photo: Hoan Nguyen Livestock farmers are also advised to supplement their animal and aquatic species with vitamins and minerals to boost their immunity during periods of prolonged hot weather and transitional seasons when outbreaks are more likely.

Deputy Director of the Department of Agriculture and Environment of Phu Tho Province, ----------------, said that vaccination, disinfection and rapid response to outbreaks of infectious diseases are still considered key tasks to minimize damage to the livestock industry.

According to -------, local governments should resolutely implement the procedure for declaring and issuing identification numbers to livestock farms in accordance with the Animal Husbandry Law, laying the foundation for a digital""" ;
