tsd:news_padi_web_toan_tinh_tiem_phong_51_370_lieu_vac_xin_cho_gia_suc_gia_cam_bao_cao_bang_dien_tu a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:toan-tinh-tiem-phong-51-370-lieu-vac-xin-cho-gia-suc-gia-cam-bao-cao-bang-dien-tu" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "dcfc2a97f87b1d2cb943bebecc0e23b1ffb458e47a98e159901c335dee2cd736" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "According to the Cao Bang Online Newspaper, 51,370 doses of vaccines were administered to livestock and poultry across the province." ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# According to the Cao Bang Online Newspaper, 51,370 doses of vaccines were administered to livestock and poultry across the province.

According to the Cao Bang Online Newspaper, 51,370 doses of vaccines were administered to livestock and poultry across the province.

Local authorities have given buffaloes and cattle 15,469 doses of foot-and-mouth disease vaccine; 17,716 doses of hemorrhagic septicemia and lumpy skin disease vaccine to buffaloes and cattle; 2,134 doses of classical swine flu vaccine; 240 doses of leptospirosis vaccine for pigs; 5,906 doses of rabies vaccine to dogs and 9,950 doses of Newcastle disease vaccine to poultry.

Veterinarians in Na Tong village of Ly Bon town vaccinate farm animals.

To improve the effectiveness of vaccination efforts, the Department of Livestock continues to coordinate with local governments to raise awareness and encourage people to fully vaccinate livestock and poultry; closely monitors the condition of livestock and develops timely disease prevention and control plans.

Strengthening disease surveillance, detection, and treatment; advising livestock farmers on regular cleaning and disinfection of animal areas; Close monitoring of the health of animals... implementation of biological safety measures in animal husbandry; Animal husbandry according to VietGAHP standards; processing of animal waste to protect the environment; Strengthening control over the transport of animals and animal products entering and leaving the territory to prevent the spread of diseases... PO Source: https://baocaobang.vn/toan-tinh-tiem-phong-51-370-lieu-vac-xin-cho-gia-suc-gia-cam-3188339.html""" ;
    ts:sourcePublishedDate "2026-05-21"^^xsd:date ;
    ts:sourcePublisher "PADI-web" ;
    ts:sourceRetrievedAt "2026-05-28T19:55:33.820746+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    ts:sourceURL "https://www.vietnam.vn/tr/toan-tinh-tiem-phong-51-370-lieu-vac-xin-cho-gia-suc-gia-cam-bao-cao-bang-dien-tu"^^xsd:anyURI .

tsd:news_padi_web_tram_chan_nuoi_va_thu_y_khu_vuc_can_duoc_khan_truong_kiem_tra_xac_minh_xu_ly_truong_hop_heo_nghi_mac_benh_dich_ta_heo_chau_phi a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:tram-chan-nuoi-va-thu-y-khu-vuc-can-duoc-khan-truong-kiem-tra-xac-minh-xu-ly-truong-hop-heo-nghi-mac-benh-dich-ta-heo-chau-phi" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "81cd9a16e7394c53613423816eb9b83c750c23290bfe324b06c95fefc385b362" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "The Can Duoc Regional Livestock and Veterinary Station investigates, verifies and urgently treats cases of pigs suspected of having African swine fever." ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# The Can Duoc Regional Livestock and Veterinary Station investigates, verifies and urgently treats cases of pigs suspected of having African swine fever.

The Can Duoc Regional Livestock and Veterinary Station investigates, verifies and urgently treats cases of pigs suspected of having African swine fever.

The station carried out rapid tests, the results of which showed that both samples tested positive for African swine fever.

Further samples were sent in for examination.

While waiting for the test results, the household decided to cull the entire stock.

On 23 May 2026, the local authorities and the household culled the 17 pigs with a total weight of 253 kg.

kg.

Then clean and disinfect the livestock area and burial pit.

Figure 1: Veterinary station in the Can Duoc area takes rapid test samples.

Figure 2.

The local authorities, in coordination with the ---------, carry out the killing of the entire pig population.

Figure 3.

Disinfection of livestock enclosures and surrounding areas in accordance with regulations.

In order to proactively prevent and control African Swine Fever (ASF), livestock farmers are asked to strictly comply with biosecurity regulations in animal husbandry: - Disinfection pits should be installed at the entrances and exits to restrict access to the livestock area for outsiders, unless absolutely necessary.

- No breeding animals of unknown origin or those that have not been subjected to quarantine may be imported.

- The transport of animals and goods related to livestock farming must be strictly controlled.

- If pigs show unusual symptoms of illness, isolate them immediately and report it to the local veterinary authority or the community people's committee.

- It is absolutely forbidden to sell sick pigs, to conceal disease outbreaks or to slaughter, transport or dispose of dead pigs in the environment without a permit.

African swine fever is a dangerous disease for which there is no effective cure.

Only good cooperation between farmers and authorities can prevent the spread of the disease.

Therefore, every farm must raise awareness of the disease and proactively implement strict disease prevention and control measures to protect its livestock, minimize economic losses, and contribute to effective disease control in the region.

Source: https://snnmt.tayninh.gov.vn/nong-nghiep/tram-chan-nuoi-va-thu-y-khu-vuc-can-duoc-khan-truong-kiem-tra-xac-minh-xu-ly-truong-hop-heo-nghi-1064990""" ;
