    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "A new outbreak of avian flu detected in a duck farm in Dordogne" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# A new outbreak of avian flu detected in a duck farm in Dordogne

A new outbreak of avian flu detected in a duck farm in Dordogne

INFO ICI PÉRIGORD - Several cases o

avian flu have been discovered in a duck farm in Saint-Laurent-des-Bâtons, in the commune of Val-de-Louyre-et-Caudeau, and confirmed on Wednesday, May 27. This is the second

utbreak detected in 2026 in the Dordogne. A new outb

eak of avian flu has been discovered in a duck farm in the Dordogne, in Saint-Laurent-des-Bâtons, according to information from ICI Périgord. The contaminati

n was confirmed on Wednesday, May 27, says the Dordogne prefecture. This is the second

ase since the beginning of 2026 in the department. An outbreak detected af

ter the death of several ducksAccording to information from ICI Périgord, the breeder from Saint-Laurent-des-Bâtons has noticed the death of several of his ducks this week. The ducklings we

e barely eight days old. The results of

he analysis laboratory confirmed that the dead animals had been contaminated by avian influenza. The farm's 7,000 duckli

gs will be slaughtered. "The State services are mo

ilized alongside the breeder, who will be compensated for the losses suffered," says the prefecture. At the end of April, the fir

st case of 2026 in the department was detected in the duck farm of the Coulounieix-Chamiers agricultural high school. The restriction measures in a

10 km perimeter in 18 municipalities around this establishment had just been lifted on Friday, May 22. All the results of analyses in poultry farms

n this area had come back negative. An area already hard hit by avian flu at the end of 2025The are

a around the new farm affected by avian flu in Saint-Laurent-des

Bâtons is very dense with poultry farms. The area had already been affected at the end of 2025. Seven outbreaks had been successi

ely confirmed in seven different breeders

rom mid-November to early December in Vergt, Saint-Amand-de-Vergt, Saint-Mayme-de-Pereyrol, Grun Bordas, Grignols and Beauregard-et-Bassac. More than 55,000 geese and ducks were slaughtered. As with each outbreak det

ction, the Dordogne prefecture has issued an order

to define restriction zones in 24 municipalities around the affected farm. A protection zone (ZP) is set up within a radius of 3 km, and a surveillance zone (ZS) within

radius of 10 km." In these perimeters, the movement of poultry and other captive birds is prohibited, except for exemptions

granted by the Departmental Directorate of Employment, Labour, Solidarity and Protection of Populations (DDETSPP)", says the prefecture. The farmers concerned are also obliged to carry out self-checks on their animals to monitor the possible spread of the virus.

Protection zone, within a radius of 3 km:Val de Louyre et Caudeau (Saint-Laurent-des-Bâtons part)Sainte-Foy-de-Longas (northern part)Saint-M

arcel-du-Périgord (northern part)Saint-Michel-de-Villadeix (southern part)Surveillance zone, within a radiu

s

of

