tsd:news_padi_web_une_semaine_apres_deux_foyers_de_grippe_aviaire_dans_des_elevages_un_troisieme_cas_suspecte_dans_le_meme_secteur_3354418_html a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:une-semaine-apres-deux-foyers-de-grippe-aviaire-dans-des-elevages-un-troisieme-cas-suspecte-dans-le-meme-secteur-3354418.html" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "33127a059c5e1cfd03d9f9f027ad51fb419bb7c8a8bfd3bedfa3dd88145000c6" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "One week after two outbreaks of avian flu on farms, a third case suspected in the same area" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# One week after two outbreaks of avian flu on farms, a third case suspected in the same area

One week after two outbreaks of avian flu on farms, a third case suspected in the same area

After two outbreaks of avian flu were discovered on the border between Tarn-et-Garonne and Haute-Garonne at the end of April 2026, a third farm is suspected of being affected by the pathogenic disease in Villemur-sur-Tarn. 
A first outbreak

was detected in Nohic in the Tarn-et-Garonne on April 28, 2026. Less than two weeks l

ter, on May 12, a second outbrea

k of avian flu was discovered in the same area, in livestock buildings located in Fronton (Haute-Garonne) and Nohic.
The ducks from this second affected farm had been vacc

i

nated, as required by the regulations. The 800 waterfowl were slaughtered. On May 20, 2026, the death o

a chicken on a farm in Villemur-su

r-Tarn (Haute-Garonne) was reported. The town hall informs that it is "most likely a case of avian influenza (High

y Pathogenic Avian Influenza (HPAI)". The prefecture of Occitanie had already put eleven municipalities in the area under surveillance. In

order to prevent the spread of the virus to other farms, several health measures ha

been reactivated. The State services specify that vigilance remains required for all poultry keepers and the d

eclaration of backyard poultry by individuals remains mandatory at all times at the town hall or online by the online procedure.""" ;
