tsd:prevention_padi_web_idn_3a3174_1 a ts:PreventionMeasure ;
    ts:hasPreventionType tss:prevention-export ;
    ts:preventionMeasureText "Change of export restrictions to Bosnia and Herzegovina in connection with HPAI  # Change of export restrictions to Bosnia and Herzegovina in connection with HPAI  Change of export restrictions to Bosnia and Herzegovina in connection with HPAI Announcements 2026-05-22 In accordance with the decision of the authorities of Bosnia and Herzegovina of 13 May 2026, due to the presence of HPAI in Poland, the export of the following goods from the Kujawsko-Pomorskie, Lubelskie, Mazowieckie, Warmińsko-Mazurskie and Wielkopolskie Voivodeships is prohibited: live poultry, ratites (including kiwi, emu, rhea and ostriches), wild game birds and other farmed and captive birds, including birds moved as companion animals; day-old chicks; hatching and consumption eggs; poultry embryos, ratites and wild game birds; fresh and frozen poultry meat, meat of ratites and wild game birds; poultry meat products, ratitebird meat and wild game birds; other products of animal origin derived from birds intended for animal, industrial or agricultural use; unprepared hunting trophies from birds and unprepared bird feathers or parts of feathers." ;
    ts:rawPreventionEvidence "export" .

